## SECTION 6: THE 15 EXAMINER TRAPS — WMA12

Check EVERY answer against ALL 15.

| # | Trap | Rule |
|---|------|------|
| T1 | CORRECT ANSWER, NO WORKING | "I got the right answer" = 0 marks on M/A questions. Every method mark requires legible working. |
| T2 | INTEGRATION WITHOUT +c | Omitting the constant of integration in indefinite integrals = lose the A mark for that expression, every time. |
| T3 | WRONG BINOMIAL COEFFICIENT | In binomial expansion, using ⁿCᵣ with wrong n (e.g. using full power not matching (1+x)^n form first) = M lost for that term. |
| T4 | DEGREES IN RADIAN QUESTION | Correct method, wrong numerical answer because student worked in degrees not radians = M awarded, A lost. Flag explicitly. |
| T5 | CHAIN RULE OMISSION | Differentiating e^(f(x)) or ln(f(x)) or sin(f(x)) without multiplying by f'(x) = M lost for that term. |
| T6 | LOG LAW ERROR | ln(a+b) treated as ln(a)+ln(b), or ln(ab) treated as ln(a)·ln(b) = M lost. Both are fundamental errors with no method credit. |
| T7 | WORKING BACKWARDS IN PROOF | In "show that" questions, starting from the given answer = 0 marks for the proof, even if all algebra is correct. |
| T8 | AREA ABOVE/BELOW AXIS | For area between curve and x-axis where curve dips below axis: treating ∫(negative region) as positive = M awarded for integration, A lost for final area. Must take modulus of negative region. |
| T9 | PARTIAL FRACTIONS WRONG FORM | Setting up wrong partial fraction form (e.g. missing repeated root structure, or wrong degree in numerator) = M lost for the decomposition. |
| T10 | ITERATION NOT CONVERGING | Stating an iterative formula is converging when it is clearly diverging, or vice versa, = lose the B mark for convergence statement. |
| T11 | TRAPEZIUM RULE: WRONG n OR h | Using wrong number of strips or wrong h value = lose B mark for h, and likely M mark for the full application. |
| T12 | FACTOR THEOREM: NOT SHOWING f(a)=0 | Claiming a factor without demonstrating f(a) = 0 explicitly = lose the B mark. Must show the substitution and result = 0. |
| T13 | INCOMPLETE GENERAL SOLUTION FOR TRIG | Solving a trig equation and giving only the principal value — no general solution — = lose A mark for missing solutions in given range. |
| T14 | IMPLICIT DIFFERENTIATION: CHAIN RULE ON y | Differentiating y terms without × dy/dx = M lost for that term. |
| T15 | DISCRIMINANT CONDITION NOT STATED | In questions asking to "find values of k for which equation has real/no real roots" — computing discriminant without stating the correct inequality condition = lose the A mark for the final answer. |

