## SECTION 8: CALIBRATION ANCHORS — WMA12

Use to calibrate before marking. Each represents a confirmed mark band on a typical WMA12 differentiation question (6 marks: M1 A1 M1 A1 M1 A1).

### ANCHOR 1 — GRADE U (~0–2/6)
**Question:** Differentiate y = 3x⁴ + e^(2x) + ln(3x) with respect to x.

> "dy/dx = 12x³ + e^(2x) + 1/x"

**CONFIRMED MARK:** 2/6 (B1 for 12x³ only, chain rule missing on both other terms)
**WHY:** e^(2x) differentiated without chain rule (missing ×2). ln(3x) → 1/x plausible via log laws but chain rule working absent. No method shown. Polynomial term alone earns independent credit.

---

### ANCHOR 2 — GRADE E (~3–4/6)
> "dy/dx = 12x³ + 2e^(2x) + 3/3x"

**CONFIRMED MARK:** 4/6
**WHY:** Chain rule applied correctly to e^(2x) — M1 A1. ln(3x) → 3/(3x) correct, simplifies to 1/x — accept. Polynomial correct B1. Unsimplified form isw — award A1.

---

### ANCHOR 3 — GRADE C (~5/6)
> "y = 3x⁴ + e^(2x) + ln(3x)
> dy/dx = 12x³ + 2e^(2x) + 1/x"

**CONFIRMED MARK:** 5/6
**WHY:** All three terms correct. Mark scheme may require explicit chain rule step on ln(3x) for final M mark. If MS accepts direct result 1/x: 6/6.

---

### ANCHOR 4 — GRADE A* (~6/6)
> "dy/dx of 3x⁴ = 12x³
> dy/dx of e^(2x) = 2e^(2x)  [chain rule: ×2]
> dy/dx of ln(3x) = (1/3x)×3 = 1/x  [chain rule: ×3]
> dy/dx = 12x³ + 2e^(2x) + 1/x"

**CONFIRMED MARK:** 6/6
**WHY:** Every chain rule step explicitly shown. Working legible at every step. All marks earned cleanly.

